translated: Fried, Karl-Axel Efraim, dentist, dental inspector, Jönköping, b. 12/8/87 in Jönköping to Axel Theodor F. and Helén Holm. Married to Märta Dahlberg in 19xx, with children: Ingvor b. 17, married to Hegen, Torsten b. 19, lieutenant, married to Ulla Oden. Education: graduated high school in Jönköping in 1908, completed dental studies in 1910, and became a licensed dentist in 1912. Worked as an assistant in Gothenburg from 1912-1913 and in Jönköping from 1913, and served as a school dentist there from 1914-1915. Participated in experimental work regarding public dental care from 1930-1935 and was the head of the dental hygiene department in Jönköping and Småland county from 1923. Served as a dental inspector in Jönköping from 1940. Was a board member of Småland Dental Association from 1914-1930 and of Jönköping Dental Association from 1930-1932, serving as the chairman from 1932-1942. Was a member of the police board and represented the city in the association for physical education. Was a board member of Småland Sports Association from 1915-1928 and served as the vice chairman from 1928-1933, and was the chairman of Jönköping's athletic club from 1916-1922. His hobby was tennis. Received the Order of Vasa and the Swedish Sports Confederation's gold medal, and was awarded a diploma of merit from Småland Sports Association.

structured.description: Karl-Axel Efraim Fried was a Swedish dentist and dental inspector from Jönköping. He was born on August 12, 1887, to Axel Theodor F. and Helén Holm in Jönköping and graduated from Jönköping High School in 1908. He completed his dental studies in 1912 and worked as a dentist in Gothenburg and Jönköping. He served as the head of the dental hygiene department in Jönköping and Småland county and as a dental inspector in Jönköping. He was a board member and chairman of Småland Dental Association and Jönköping Dental Association, respectively. He was also a member of the police board, represented the city in the Association for Physical Education, and served as a board member and chairman of Småland Sports Association and Jönköping Athletic Club. He had a hobby of playing tennis and received several awards and recognitions, including the Order of Vasa, the Swedish Sports Confederation's Gold Medal, and Småland Sports Association's Diploma of Merit.
